	<td valign="middle">
		<span style="font-family:arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">Day of Defeat Beta 3.0</span><span class="small">&nbsp;&nbsp;by G.Bloke at 18:06:33 GMT</span>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td valign="middle">
		<p><a href="http://www.dayofdefeatmod.com/" target="_BLANK" class="pagelink">Day of Defeat</a> Beta 3.0 is due for release sometime in the next week, the developers are keeping the exact date a mystery.
<br>
<br>The WW2 Halflife modifaction has had a rocky past but it now has official support from Valve (the developers of Halflife) which suggest things are on the right track. The new beta boasts, well nothing ... aside from the mention of three new maps the DoD team has said very little about what changes have been made, probably on the assumption that everyone has been privy to little leaks and conversations on their forums. I guess like the release date it will all remain a mystery until the time comes.
<br>
<br>Personally I won&#39;t be getting heavily involved in any game based on the halflife engine, which is so heavily compromised now by cheats that theres little fun left to be had. However, DoD showed real promise in the very first beta and if your a WW2 fan then this might just be of interest to you.</p>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td valign="middle" align="right">
